text: Designer Emilia Wickstead has backtracked on her claim that Meghan's £200, 000 Givenchy gown looked'identical'to one of her own designs. In a statement, the New Zealand - born designer said she does'not think that her wedding dress was a copy of any of our designs ', adding that she has the'greatest respect for Clare Waight Keller '. Emilia, 34, described the Duchess of Sussex as looking'absolutely beautiful'on her wedding day and said she has the'utmost admiration and respect for her '. It comes after she the designer previously suggested to the Mail that Meghan's wedding gown was'identical to one of our dresses '.
